REFERENDUM campaigners clashed in Glasgow City centre as Labour MPs met in Buchanan Street for a rally. Miliband heckled in city centre REFERENDUM campaigners clashed in Glasgow City centre as Labour MPs met in Buchanan Street for a rally.Ed Miliband addressed the No campaigners, who included shadow cabinet members Yvette Cooper and Andy Burnham and former Home Secretary Jack Straw. at the steps outside the Concert Hall.Rival Yes campaigner tried to drown out the speakers and people from both sides were chanting &quot;Scotland says yes&quot; and &quot;Scotland says no&quot; as several police officers looked on. At one point officers had to separate people from both sides.The MPs had travelled north on the train from London before walking through the city centre followed by a small group of Yes supporters who heckled the politicians. 